.E.]]<ref name= autoevolution_Renault_ZE_Concept20090910 /><ref name= green.autoblog.com_Renault_ZE_Concept20090916 />\n* [[SEAT Ibiza|SEAT Ibz concept]]\n*[[Tesla Model S]]\n* Trabant nT\n*[[Toyota Auris#Hybrid|Toyota Auris HSD]] Full Hybrid Concept\n*[[Toyota iQ Sport]]\n*[[Toyota Prius Plug-In Hybrid Concept]]\n* [[Volkswagen up!|Volkswagen E-Up]]\n* [[Volkswagen L1]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===2011===\n[[File:Grey Mini Cooper SD Clubman IAA 2011.JPG|thumb|right|[[Mini Clubman (2007)|Mini Clubman]]]]\n[[File:Renault Twingo pink.jpg|thumb|right|[[Renault Twingo]]]]\n[[File:Silver Fisker Surf fl IAA 2011.jpg|thumb|right|[[Fisker Surf]]]]\n[[File:VW Nils small.jpg|thumb|[[Volkswagen Nils]]]]\n[[File:BMW i8 Concept IAA.jpg|thumb|[[BMW i8]]]]\nThe 2011 show was held from 13 September to 25 September.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.iaa.de/en/besucher/dates/ |title=IAA 65th International Motor Show \u2013 Dates and Hours |accessdate=2013-05-01 |publisher=IAA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801072610/http://www.iaa.de/en/besucher/dates/ |archivedate=2013-08-01 }}</ref> The 64th edition of the show included 1,012 exhibitors from 32 countries and was attended by more than 928,000 visitors from 105 countries, 36% of them being trade visitors, among those 80% from the automotive industry, plus more than 12'000 accredited journalists from 98 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.automobil-produktion.de/2011/09/iaa-2011-mit-neuem-besucherrekord/|title=AUTOMOBIL PRODUKTION \u2013 AUTOMOBIL PRODUKTION Online|website=www.automobil-produktion.de|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927173518/http://www.automobil-produktion.de/2011/09/iaa-2011-mit-neuem-besucherrekord/|archivedate=2013-09-27}}</ref> 183 world premieres were unveiled.\n\n====Production cars====\n{{Div col}}\n\n*2012 [[Abarth]] 695 Competizione\n*2012 [[Alfa Romeo MiTo]] 0.9 TwinAir 85\n*2011 [[Alpina B6 (F12)|Alpina B6 Biturbo cabriolet]]\n*2012 [[Aston Martin DBS]] Carbon Edition\n*2012 [[Audi A5]]/[[Audi S5|S5]] (facelift)\n*2012 [[Audi S6]]\n*2012 [[Audi S7]]\n*2012 [[Audi S8]]\n*2012 [[Audi R8 (road car)|Audi R8]] GT Spyder\n*2012 [[Bentley Continental GTC]]\n*2012 [[BMW 1]]\n*2012 [[BMW M5]]\n*2012 [[Chevrolet Camaro]] (European version)\n*2012 [[Chevrolet Malibu]] (European version)\n*2012 [[Citroen DS5]]\n*2012 [[Ferrari 458 Spider]]\n*2012 [[Fiat Panda#Gen3|Fiat Panda]]\n*2012 [[Ford Fiesta]] ECOnetic\n*2012 [[Ford Focus (third generation)|Ford Focus ST]] (production version)\n*2011 [[Honda Civic (ninth generation)|Honda Civic]] (European version)\n*2012 [[Hyundai i30]]\n*2012 [[Jaguar XF]]\n*2012 [[Jeep Wrangler]] 3.6 V6\n*[[Kia K9]]\n*2012 [[Kia Rio]] 3-door\n*2012 [[Lamborghini Gallardo]] LP570-4\n*2012 [[Chrysler 200|Lancia Flavia Cabrio]]\n*2012 [[Chrysler 300#Second generation|Lancia Thema]]\n*2012 [[Chrysler Voyager#Generation V|Lancia Voyager]]\n*2013 [[Lexus GS 350]]\n*2013 [[Lotus Exige S]]\n*2012 [[Mazda CX-5]]\n*2012 [[Mercedes-Benz B-Class]]\n*[[Mia electric]]\n*[[Mini Coup\u00e9]]\n*2012 [[Opel Astra|Opel/Vauxhall Astra]] GTC\n*2012 [[Opel Combo|Opel/Vauxhall Combo]]\n*2012 [[Opel Zafira Tourer|Opel/Vauxhall Zafira Tourer]]\n*2012 [[Peugeot 508]] RXH Diesel Hybrid\n*2012 [[Porsche 991|Porsche 911]] Carrera\n*2011 [[Radical Sportscars]] SR3 SL\n*2012 [[Renault Koleos]] (facelift)\n*2012 [[Renault Twingo]] (facelift)\n*2012 [[SEAT Exeo]] (facelift)\n*2012 [[smart fortwo]] electric\n*2012 [[Subaru XV]]\n*2012 [[Suzuki Swift]] Sport\n*2012 [[Toyota Avensis]] (facelift)\n*2012 [[Toyota Prius+]] (European version)\n*2012 [[Toyota Yaris]]\n*2012 [[Volkswagen up!]]\n*Yo-Mobil\n{{Div col end}}\n\n====Concept cars====\n{{Div col}}\n*[[Alfa Romeo 4C]]\n*[[Audi A2]] Concept\n*[[Audi Urban Concept]]\n*[[Audi Urban Spyder Concept]]\n*[[BMW i3]]\n*[[BMW i8]]\n*[[Chevrolet Miray]]\n*[[Citro\u00ebn Tubik]]\n*[[Eterniti Motors]] Hemera<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/News/NewsArticle.aspx?AR=258644 |title=Autocar 16 August 2011 |publisher=Autocar.co.uk |date=2011-08-16 |accessdate=2011-08-28}}</ref>\n*[[Fisker Karma|Fisker Surf]]\n*[[Ford Evos]]\n*[[Ford Fiesta ST]] Concept\n*[[Infiniti FX]] Sebastian Vettel Concept\n*[[Jaguar C-X16]]\n*[[Kia GT Concept]]\n*[[Land Rover DC100]]\n*[[Maserati Kubang]]\n*[[Mercedes-Benz B-Class]] E-CELL Plus Concept\n*[[Mercedes-Benz F125]]\n*[[Mitsubishi PX-MiEV]]\n*[[Opel RAK e]]\n*[[Peugeot HX1]]\n*[[Renault Frendzy]] Electric Concept\n*[[Rimac Concept One]] Electric Supercar\n*[[SEAT IBL]]\n*[[Skoda Mission L]]\n*[[Smart forvision]]\n*[[SsangYong XUV-1]]\n*[[Volkswagen Beetle]] R Concept\n*[[Volkswagen Up!|Volkswagen Buggy up!]]\n*[[Volkswagen Nils]]\n*[[Volvo Concept You]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===2013===\n[[File:2013 IAA DSC01972 DxO (9879472923) (2).jpg|thumb|Inside the [[Porsche]] pavilion at the IAA 2013]]\nThe 2013 show took place from 10 September to 22 September.\n\n[[Nissan]] introduced a \"smart watch\" that measures the user's heart rate, temperature and other biometrics. It is also able to keep a watch on car data like fuel efficiency and average speed. It was developed by Nissan's [[Nismo]] laboratory. They currently capture live [[biometric]] and [[telematics]] data from Nissan racing cars and their drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-23964797|title=Nissan launches driver's smartwatch|first=Jane|last=Wakefield|date=2013-09-09|via=www.bbc.co.uk|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130910051229/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-23964797|archivedate=2013-09-10}}</ref>\n\n====Production cars====\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Abarth]] 595 50 Anniversario<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-2013-abarth-595-50th-anniversary-edition-live-photos-66890.html|title=Frankfurt 2013: Abarth 595 50th Anniversary Edition|work=Autoevolution|accessdate=2014-01-28|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202174427/http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-201