o 22 September.\n\n[[Nissan]] introduced a \"smart watch\" that measures the user's heart rate, temperature and other biometrics. It is also able to keep a watch on car data like fuel efficiency and average speed. It was developed by Nissan's [[Nismo]] laboratory. They currently capture live [[biometric]] and [[telematics]] data from Nissan racing cars and their drivers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-23964797|title=Nissan launches driver's smartwatch|first=Jane|last=Wakefield|date=2013-09-09|via=www.bbc.co.uk|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130910051229/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-23964797|archivedate=2013-09-10}}</ref>\n\n====Production cars====\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Abarth]] 595 50 Anniversario<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-2013-abarth-595-50th-anniversary-edition-live-photos-66890.html|title=Frankfurt 2013: Abarth 595 50th Anniversary Edition|work=Autoevolution|accessdate=2014-01-28|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202174427/http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-2013-abarth-595-50th-anniversary-edition-live-photos-66890.html|archivedate=2014-02-02}}</ref>\n* [[Abarth]] 695 Tributo Maserati<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-2013-abarth-695-tributo-maserati-in-record-grey-live-photos-66896.html|title=Frankfurt 2013: Abarth 695 Tributo Maserati in Record Grey|work=Autoevolution|accessdate=2014-01-28|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202174433/http://www.autoevolution.com/news/frankfurt-2013-abarth-695-tributo-maserati-in-record-grey-live-photos-66896.html|archivedate=2014-02-02}}</ref>\n* 2014 [[Alfa Romeo Giulietta (2010)|Alfa Romeo Giulietta]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/113091362928/2014-alfa-romeo-giulietta-brings-its-modest-facelift-to|title=2014 Alfa Romeo Giulietta brings its modest facelift to Frankfurt|work=Worldcarfans|accessdate=2014-01-28|url-status=live|archiv